cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY

The paper proposes a privacy-preserving distributed machine learning framework that focuses on privacy concerns in training data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses privacy concerns, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper proposes a framework that provides heterogeneous privacy for users, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CY (Computers and Society).
